<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[714,1248,845,1332]" box="[749,825,845,871]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[749,825,845,871]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">group.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[714,1248,845,1332]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Specimens from 
<taxonomicName authority="var. tenuifolia" box="[934,1247,876,903]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Merciera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="tenuifolia" variety="tenuifolia">
<emphasis box="[934,1081,876,903]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">M. tenuifolia</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1142,1247,877,903]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
constitute this group. No single quantitative character (
<figureCitation box="[832,899,938,964]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[151,179,1610,1627]" captionTargetBox="[173,1227,1206,1572]" captionTargetId="figure-90@5.[156,1227,1204,1580]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 4. — Box and whisker plots depicting the character variation ranges in the six phenetic groups: A, bract length; B, hypanthium length; C, calyx lobe length; D, corolla tube length; E, corolla lobe length; F, style length; G, filament length; H, leaf length; I, leaf width." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4605187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4605187/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) separates this group from the other violet-blue flowered groups (A3 and A4). However, the distinctly ascending leaves separate this group from all the other groups. Geographically, this group occurs in sympatry with the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Adamson" authorityYear="1955" baseAuthorityName="Schltr." box="[755,1013,1090,1117]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Merciera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="tenuifolia" variety="azurea">
<emphasis box="[755,892,1091,1117]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">M. tenuifolia</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[944,1013,1091,1116]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group but does differ from it in having a more erect habit. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="ADAMSON R. S." box="[714,906,1153,1179]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" pagination="157 - 163" refId="ref5416" refString="ADAMSON R. S. 1954. - The genus Merciera. J. S. African Bot. 20: 157 - 163." type="journal article" year="1954">ADAMSON (1954)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[917,1024,1152,1177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Merciera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="azurea">
<emphasis box="[917,1024,1152,1177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">M. azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only a smaller and stouter form of 
<taxonomicName box="[890,1030,1182,1209]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Merciera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis box="[890,914,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[931,1030,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and he accordingly assigned it varietal status. The distance between the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Adamson" authorityYear="1955" baseAuthorityName="Schltr." box="[755,1012,1244,1271]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Merciera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="tenuifolia" variety="azurea">
<emphasis box="[755,892,1244,1271]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">M. tenuifolia</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[943,1012,1244,1269]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">azurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="var. tenuifolia" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Merciera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="tenuifolia" variety="tenuifolia">
<emphasis box="[1065,1202,1244,1271]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">M. tenuifolia</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[714,811,1275,1301]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clusters revealed by CA and PCO do not support ADAMSON’ s concept of taxon boundaries.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
